lyhedra. On this basis, a number of problems are solved using a new approach, such as the embeddability of a graph on a surface (orientable and nonorientable) with given genus, the Gauss crossing conjecture, the graphicness and cographicness of a matroid, and so forth. Notably, the specific case of embeddability on a surface of genus zero leads to a number of corollaries, including the theorems of Lefschetz (on double coverings), of MacLane (on cycle bases), and of Whitney (on duality) for planarity. Relevant problems include the Jordan axiom in polyhedral forms, efficient methods for extremality and for recognizing a variety of embeddings (including rectilinear layouts in VLSI), and pan-polynomials, including those of Jones, Kauffman (on knots), and Tutte (on graphs), among others. Contents Preliminaries Polyhedra Surfaces Homology on Polyhedra Polyhedra on the Sphere Automorphisms of a Polyhedron Gauss Crossing Sequences Cohomology on Graphs Embeddability on Surfaces Embeddings on Sphere Orthogonality on Surfaces Net Embeddings Extremality on Surfaces Matroidal Graphicness Knot Polynomials  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aTopological graph theory. 7aMATHEMATICS / Discrete Mathematics.2bisacsh1 aUniversity of Science & Technology,.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics 2017z9783110548204oZDB-23-DMA0 cEPUBz97831104792250 cprintz978311047669940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311047949240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110479492423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/97